.TH GET.OTUREP 1 2024-Feb "" "Get the representative sequence"
.SH NAME
get.oturep \- get.oturep(dist, contig.unique.fasta, list,
    <i>label</i> = <span style='color: green;'>0.03</span>,
    <i>logfile</i> = [13]get.oturep.txt)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fIget.oturep(dist, contig.unique.fasta, list,
    <i>label</i> = <span style='color: green;'>0.03</span>,
    <i>logfile</i> = [13]get.oturep.txt)\fR
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\fBdist\fB \fR\- . 
.PP
.PP
\fBcontig.unique.fasta\fB \fR\- . 
.PP
.PP
\fBlist\fB \fR\- . 
.PP
.PP
\fBlabel\fB \fR\- 0.03. 
.PP
.PP
\fBlogfile\fB \fR\- [13]get.oturep.txt. 
.PP
.SH DETAILS
.PP
While the ``bin.seqs`` command reports the OTU number for all sequences, the ``get.oturep`` command generates a fasta-formatted sequence file containing only a representative sequence for each OTU. A .rep.fasta and .rep.name file or .rep.count_table file is generated for each OTU definition.
.PP
